= Atomic Claim Selection and Validation =

{{info}}
**Developer Reference** - Current implementation of pre-job AtomicClaim selection, prepared Stage 1 reuse, interactive and automatic ACS modes, and the ACS-based validation tooling path.

**Status as of 2026-04-29**: The ACS product path and validation tooling are implemented. Selected-claim coverage starvation is now guarded by Stage 2 telemetry plus budget-aware admission. Current file-backed budget defaults enable ##claimSelectionBudgetAwarenessEnabled## with ##claimSelectionBudgetFitMode = "allow_fewer_recommendations"## and an effective local admission cap of 3 under the default 600s/120s research budget. Automatic ACS remains supported and now surfaces selected-claim coverage, budget treatment, submission path, and run-provenance metadata.

**Key Files**: ##claim-selection-flow.ts##, ##claim-selection-recommendation.ts##, ##research-waste-metrics.ts##, ##internal-runner-queue.ts##, ##claimboundary-pipeline.ts##, ##ClaimSelectionDraftService.cs##, ##ClaimSelectionDraftsController.cs##, ##JobService.cs##, ##automatic-claim-selection.js##
{{/info}}

== 1. Purpose ==

Atomic Claim Selection (ACS) is the pre-job intake path that lets FactHarbor prepare the final Stage 1 ##AtomicClaim## candidate set before the final report job is created.

The implementation has two connected responsibilities:

* Product ACS: prepare Stage 1 once, let the user or automatic mode choose which already-valid ##AtomicClaim## IDs proceed, then run Stage 2+ only for those IDs.
* Validation ACS: make non-interactive validation automation use the same ACS automatic draft path, while emitting passive metadata that explains prepared, ranked, recommended, deferred, not-selected, and finally analyzed claim IDs.

ACS does **not** create a new analytical meaning layer. It does not merge, split, rewrite, or semantically reinterpret claims after Stage 1. It selects from the exact ##AtomicClaim## IDs emitted by the current Stage 1 pipeline.

== 2. Current Runtime Posture ==

|= Area |= Current implementation
| Default product mode | ##interactive## in file-backed defaults and current local UCM after the 2026-04-28 canary.
| Selection cap | ##claimSelectionCap##, normalized to 1..5. Current file-backed default is ##5##.
| Automatic mode | Supported, but it still goes through claim-selection drafts and selected-ID validation. It is not a direct all-claim job path.
| Budget-aware recommendation | Implemented and enabled in file-backed defaults. Active runtime can tune ##claimSelectionBudgetAwarenessEnabled##, ##claimSelectionBudgetFitMode##, and ##claimSelectionEstimatedMainResearchMsPerClaim##.
| Validation tooling | Supported validation scripts submit through ##apps/web/scripts/automatic-claim-selection.js## and emit ##submissionPath: "acs-automatic-draft"##.
| Entrypoint provenance | ##JobEntity.SubmissionPath## identifies direct API, retry, ACS interactive draft, and ACS automatic draft jobs. Admin job details expose creation/execution/prompt hashes for validation attribution.
| Open quality finding | Post-fix canaries no longer show zero targeted selected claims under the effective admission cap. Remaining findings are report-quality adjudication drift on Bolsonaro and long-tail applicability/clustering/verdict runtime.

== 3. Product Flow ==

{{mermaid}}
flowchart TD
    start["Analyze request"]
    mode["Resolve selection mode from request or UCM"]
    draft["Create ClaimSelectionDraftEntity"]
    prepare["Prepare Stage 1 snapshot"]
    candidates["Final Stage 1 AtomicClaim candidates"]
    belowCap{"Candidate count within admission cap?"}
    recommend["Run batched ACS recommendation"]
    interactive{"Selection mode interactive?"}
    manual["User reviews and confirms selectedClaimIds"]
    auto["Automatic mode confirms recommendedClaimIds"]
    job["Create draft-backed JobEntity"]
    run["Run ClaimAssessmentBoundary Stage 2+ over selected AtomicClaims"]
    result["Persist report result"]

    start --> mode
    mode --> draft
    draft --> prepare
    prepare --> candidates
    candidates --> belowCap
    belowCap -->|"yes"| job
    belowCap -->|"no"| recommend
    recommend --> interactive
    interactive -->|"yes"| manual
    interactive -->|"no"| auto
    manual --> job
    auto --> job
    job --> run
    run --> result
{{/mermaid}}

The within-cap path auto-continues without showing the chooser because there is no selection pressure: all valid candidates fit within the configured admission cap. Once the candidate count exceeds the admission cap, the recommendation and selection surface become relevant.

== 4. Draft State Machine ==

{{mermaid}}
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> QUEUED
    QUEUED --> PREPARING: runner starts draft preparation
    PREPARING --> AWAITING_CLAIM_SELECTION: interactive selection required
    PREPARING --> COMPLETED: below-cap auto-continue or automatic recommendation confirmed
    AWAITING_CLAIM_SELECTION --> COMPLETED: confirm selectedClaimIds
    AWAITING_CLAIM_SELECTION --> PREPARING: Other / retry
    AWAITING_CLAIM_SELECTION --> CANCELLED: cancel
    PREPARING --> FAILED: preparation failure
    QUEUED --> EXPIRED: lazy expiry
    PREPARING --> EXPIRED: lazy expiry
    AWAITING_CLAIM_SELECTION --> EXPIRED: lazy expiry
    COMPLETED --> [*]
    FAILED --> [*]
    CANCELLED --> [*]
    EXPIRED --> [*]
{{/mermaid}}

Important state behavior:

* ##AWAITING_CLAIM_SELECTION## is a first-class state for product sessions.
* In validation automation, ##AWAITING_CLAIM_SELECTION## is a structured terminal outcome because an automatic validation run must not silently require a human click.
* ##COMPLETED## means the draft has produced a final job, not that the final analysis job has finished.

== 5. Prepared Stage 1 Reuse ==

{{mermaid}}
flowchart LR
    draft["ClaimSelectionDraftEntity"]
    prep["PreparedStage1Snapshot"]
    selection["ClaimSelectionJson"]
    job["JobEntity"]
    provenance["Provenance guard"]
    filter["Filter prepared understanding by selectedClaimIds"]
    stage2["Stage 2 research"]
    stage3["Stage 3 ClaimAssessmentBoundary clustering"]
    stage4["Stage 4 verdict generation"]
    stage5["Stage 5 aggregation"]
    observability["analysisObservability.acsResearchWaste"]

    draft --> prep
    draft --> selection
    prep --> job
    selection --> job
    job --> provenance
    provenance --> filter
    filter --> stage2
    stage2 --> stage3
    stage3 --> stage4
    stage4 --> stage5
    stage2 --> observability
{{/mermaid}}

The final job reuses ##PreparedStage1Json## and ##ClaimSelectionJson## persisted from the draft. The runner validates that:

* ##ClaimSelectionJson.selectedClaimIds## exists and is non-empty.
* selected IDs are unique.
* selected IDs exist in the prepared candidate set.
* prepared Stage 1 provenance still matches analysis-affecting runtime state.

The prepared Stage 1 provenance deliberately ignores already-persisted ACS orchestration knobs, such as default mode and idle timeout, because those should not invalidate an already prepared candidate set. The persisted ##selectionCap## remains separately checked.

== 6. Recommendation Contract ==

The recommendation is one batched LLM call over the final Stage 1 candidates. It ranks and recommends from already-surviving candidates; it is not Gate 1 authority.

|= Field |= Meaning
| ##rankedClaimIds## | Complete ranking over the final candidate IDs.
| ##recommendedClaimIds## | IDs recommended for selection, capped by ##claimSelectionCap##.
| ##selectedClaimIds## | IDs actually confirmed for final analysis.
| ##deferredClaimIds## | Explicit budget-deferred IDs when budget-aware mode allows fewer recommendations.
| ##notRecommendedClaimIds## | Structural summary: ranked IDs not recommended.
| ##notSelectedClaimIds## | Structural summary: prepared IDs not selected.
| ##budgetFitMode## | UCM-controlled behavior: ##off##, ##explain_only##, or ##allow_fewer_recommendations##.

Do not treat ordinary unselected claims as budget-deferred claims. ##deferredClaimIds## means explicit budget-aware allow-fewer metadata only.

== 7. Validation Thin Waist ==

Supported validation automation is intentionally narrow. Validation scripts submit through the shared ACS client, then read existing metadata. They do not add direct-full reruns, prompt changes, extra searches, or extra LLM work.

{{mermaid}}
flowchart TD
    scripts["Supported validation scripts"]
    client["Shared ACS validation client"]
    draft["POST /api/fh/claim-selection-drafts selectionMode=automatic"]
    waitDraft["Poll draft until finalJobId or terminal draft status"]
    waitJob["Poll final job until terminal job status"]
    admin["Admin-aware job detail fetch"]
    summary["Schema v2 validation summary"]
    refs["Captain-approved historical direct references"]
    review["Review matrix and pipeline findings"]

    scripts --> client
    client --> draft
    draft --> waitDraft
    waitDraft --> waitJob
    waitJob --> admin
    admin --> summary
    refs --> review
    summary --> review
{{/mermaid}}

Supported validation callers:

|= Script |= Current disposition
| ##scripts/validation/extract-validation-summary.js## | Supported. Uses the shared ACS client.
| ##scripts/run-validation-matrix.js## | Supported. Uses the shared ACS client and preserves historical reference fields on failure rows.
| ##apps/web/scripts/baseline-runner.js## | Supported. Uses the shared ACS client and schema v2 fields.

Quarantined or legacy callers:

|= Script |= Disposition
| ##scripts/Benchmarks/phaseA_search_experiment.py## | Quarantined as benchmark/forensic unless migrated.
| ##scripts/Benchmarks/phase1_experiment.py## | Quarantined as benchmark/forensic unless migrated.
| ##scripts/inverse-scope-regression.ps1## | Quarantined until migrated through the shared ACS client.
| ##scripts/run-regression.ps1## | Quarantined until migrated through the shared ACS client.
| ##scripts/run-baseline.ps1## | Quarantined legacy direct helper; use the JS baseline runner for supported ACS validation.
| ##scripts/submit-hydrogen-job.ps1## | Quarantined ad hoc helper.
| ##apps/web/test/scripts/regression-test.js## | Quarantined because the inputs and old result parsing are stale for supported validation.

== 8. Validation Summary Schema ==

The shared ACS validation client emits schema v2 summaries from existing draft, job, and result state.

|= Field group |= Representative fields |= Source
| Submission/provenance | ##schemaVersion##, ##submissionPath##, ##draftId##, ##jobId##, ##draftStatus##, ##jobStatus##, ##gitCommitHash##, ##createdGitCommitHash##, ##executedWebGitCommitHash##, ##promptContentHash##, ##analysisRunProvenance## | Draft/job response plus result metadata.
| Prepared/ranked/recommended | ##preparedClaimIds##, ##rankedClaimIds##, ##recommendedClaimIds## | ##PreparedStage1Json## and ##ClaimSelectionJson##.
| Selection collapse | ##selectedClaimIds##, ##notSelectedClaimIds##, ##notRecommendedClaimIds##, ##deferredClaimIds## | Derived structurally from prepared/ranked/recommended/selected IDs.
| Budget treatment | ##budgetFitRationale##, ##budgetTreatmentCounts##, ##budgetTreatmentByClaimId## | ##ClaimSelectionJson## recommendation metadata.
| Report shape | ##truthPercentage##, ##verdict##, ##confidence##, ##claimVerdictCount##, ##claimBoundaryCount##, ##evidenceCount##, ##sourceCount## | ##ResultJson##.
| Stage 2 ACS telemetry | ##selectedClaimResearchCoverage##, ##selectedClaimResearch##, ##zeroTargetedSelectedClaimCount##, ##zeroTargetedSelectedClaimIds##, ##contradictionReachability## | ##resultJson.analysisObservability.acsResearchWaste##.
| Historical references | ##historicalDirectReferenceJobId##, ##historicalDirectReferenceQuality##, ##historicalDirectReferenceJobStatus## | ##scripts/validation/captain-approved-families.json##.
| Metadata health | ##metadataUnavailable##, ##metadataUnavailableReason## | Client extraction result.

Historical direct references are attribution metadata only. They explain how a current ACS run differs from a known old direct job; they are not a request to rerun direct all-claim analysis.

== 9. Current Live Finding ==

The 2026-04-29 selected-claim starvation fix was validated with six live jobs.

|= Job |= Input |= Result
| ##a652605b34cc430c9eb424bd9188fae7## | SVP PDF | Phase-1-only canary selected 5 and still produced ##zeroTargetedSelectedClaimCount = 2##. This validated the need for budget admission.
| ##60f8e2287a07446fb80edf4ff89e8cc8## | SVP PDF | Budget-aware canary selected 3 with admission cap 3 and ##zeroTargetedSelectedClaimCount = 0##.
| ##661a649d61444be1b4c7a511bc8df2a6## | SVP PDF repeat | Selected 3 with ##zeroTargetedSelectedClaimCount = 0##; separate verdict-integrity warnings remain a report-quality issue.
| ##1b77e64cebac44da87a075a5977a3bf3## | Bolsonaro fair-trial extended input | Pre exact-cap correction: prepared 3/admission cap 3, but recommendation selected only one claim. This exposed the exact-cap bug.
| ##aa686dcce9d544a3a0d93a17e5860b67## | Bolsonaro fair-trial extended input | Exact-cap path selected all 3, ##zeroTargetedSelectedClaimCount = 0##, result ##UNVERIFIED## 52.5/40.
| ##685fbe2dc6674dfa91a3a741eaa57b9c## | Bolsonaro fair-trial extended repeat | Exact-cap path selected all 3, ##zeroTargetedSelectedClaimCount = 0##, result ##UNVERIFIED## 48.5/40.

The current implementation lesson is split:

* Selected-claim coverage/admission is fixed for the tested paths. Under the local default budget, the effective admission cap is 3 and all selected claims in post-fix canaries received searched main research.
* The Bolsonaro result is now an adjudication/report-quality follow-up, not an acquisition miss: both post-fix runs had sufficient searched evidence for all selected claims but remained ##UNVERIFIED##, while older exact-extended baselines were usually ##LEANING-TRUE## or ##MOSTLY-TRUE##.

== 10. API and Storage Surfaces ==

|= Surface |= Responsibility
| ##ClaimSelectionDraftEntity## | Pre-job session, status/progress, active input, selection mode, access-token hash, draft state JSON, final job link, hidden flag.
| ##ClaimSelectionDraftEventEntity## | Audit trail for draft actions and status transitions.
| ##JobEntity.ClaimSelectionDraftId## | Links a final job to its draft. Unique index prevents duplicate final jobs per draft.
| ##JobEntity.SubmissionPath## | Records whether a job came from direct API, retry, ACS interactive draft, or ACS automatic draft submission.
| ##JobEntity.PreparedStage1Json## | Persisted prepared Stage 1 snapshot for draft-backed execution.
| ##JobEntity.ClaimSelectionJson## | Persisted selection metadata for the final job.
| ##POST /v1/claim-selection-drafts## | API draft creation.
| ##POST /v1/claim-selection-drafts/{draftId}/confirm## | Confirms selected IDs and creates the final job.
| ##GET /api/fh/jobs/{jobId}## with admin key | Web proxy that exposes prepared/selection metadata for validation summaries.

== 11. Operational Rules ==

* Commit source changes before submitting live validation jobs, then restart or reseed affected services if needed.
* Keep UCM mode ##interactive## for ordinary product usage unless the Captain explicitly switches it.
* Use only Captain-approved inputs for validation jobs.
* Treat ##UNVERIFIED## as suspicious until inspected under the AGENTS.md UNVERIFIED ambiguity discipline.
* Validation tooling should report structural findings; it should not hide, reinterpret, or "fix" pipeline-quality problems.
* Do not add direct-full rerun modes to validation automation unless Captain explicitly approves a new architecture.

== 12. Follow-Ups ==

|= Item |= Why it remains open
| Stage 2 selected-claim research distribution | Fixed for tested draft-backed paths through coverage telemetry and budget-aware admission; keep monitoring canaries for regressions.
| Budget-aware ACS promotion | Promoted locally with ##allow_fewer_recommendations## and a persisted admission cap; tune only from canary timing evidence.
| API-level direct endpoint governance | Direct ##/v1/analyze## still exists for product/API use; blocking or policy enforcement is a separate design task.
| Provenance interpretation | Creation-time, prepared, executed, and prompt hashes are now surfaced together. Follow-up work should classify material drift rather than assuming one hash is enough.
| Prompt-surface migration decisions | Prompt-governance exceptions are now registered, but SR core, grounding-check legacy, Stage 1 inline framing, SR evidence-pack inline helpers, and inverse calibration prompt handling still need explicit long-term decisions.
| Stage 1 time-to-selection | Heavy URL/PDF inputs still spend meaningful time in full Stage 1 preparation before the selector appears.
| Post-acquisition long-tail latency | Applicability/claim mapping, clustering, and verdict debate can still dominate runtime after selected-claim acquisition is healthy.
| Bolsonaro adjudication drift | Current exact-cap ACS runs remain ##UNVERIFIED## despite healthy acquisition; compare against historical exact-extended baselines in a separate report-quality slice.

